works.description: For the adventurous journeys beyond the blue sky, there is a stiff competition going on between the space tourism companies. While the affluent have already spent a whopping $200,000 a ticket for 2.5-hour flight aboard the SpaceShipTwo, experts believe we can really expect cheaper suborbital spaceflights in the near future, with a ticket most probably costing between $50,000 and $100,000.
